            "answer_text": "Costa Rica has never gone to war with any other countries*. As it now has no armed forces (other than the Public Force, a gendarmerie) it\u2019s unlikely ever to go to war again. Probably not coincidentally, Costa Rica is one of the most stable, prosperous, and progressive nations in Latin America.  * It did have two civil wars, one after independence, and the Civil War of 1948. It also declared war on Germany during both WW1 and WW2, but this was purely a diplomatic gesture - it sent no troops to fight in either case. ",
